devdoc.details: Aggregate Account needs to be set for Asset

params.accountName_: The name of the aggregate account
params.isStable_: Tells if this aggregate holds stable assets or not

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

isStable.details: will be needed for interpool swapping

devdoc.title: AggregateAccount

accountName().notice: name of the account. E.g BTC for aggregate account containing zBTC, BTC.e, ETH etc.

isStable().notice: true if the assets represented by the aggregate are stablecoins

setAccountName(string).notice: Changes Account Name. Can only be set by the contract owner.
